OL,3,CMan admits killing wife in Belfast home
OL,5,FA 64-year-old man who killed his wife
OL,6,Fin a hammer attack in their Four Winds
OL,7,Fhome in Belfast will be sentenced for
OL,8,Fher manslaughter in July.JGary
OL,9,FAlexander Baird appeared in the dock
OL,10,Fof Belfast Crown Court on Monday where
OL,11,Fhe pleaded guilty to a charge of the
OL,12,Fmanslaughter of his wife Susan Baird
OL,13,Fby way of diminished responsibility.
OL,14,FThe 60-year- old mother-of-four died
OL,15,Ffrom catastrophic head injures in her
OL,16,FWindermere Road home on the afternoon
OL,17,Fof Sunday August 16, 2020.JAt the time
OL,18,Fof her death, she worked as an
OL,19,Fadministrator at Orangefield
OL,20,FPresbyterian Church.JAt 4.51pm on the
OL,21,Fday in question Gary Baird - a former
OL,22,FBBC security guard - called 999 and
OL,23,Fsaid "I've just murdered my wife".JHe
OL,24,Ftold the operator he had hit her with
OL,25,Fa hammer and when asked if she was
OL,26,Fdead, Baird replied: "I think so."
